topic: History Workflow Series ("Literary Movements and Divine Comedy explorative search")

goals.1: Who wrote The Divine Comedy? (return the IRI and the label of the author)
goals.3: Identify the BGP for literary movement
goals.4: Return the poets born in the same place of the author of The Divine Comedy who are born between 1300 and 1500 (1300 and 1500 included) (the result set must be a list of couples poets IRI and label).
goals.5: Identify the BGP for literary work
goals.6: Compare the author of The Divine Comedy with Giovanni Boccaccio. Return for these poets the number of literary work they wrote (the result set must be two triples -one for each author- author IRI, label and #literary work).
goals.7: Consider italian poets, their place of birth (the city) and their university education. Return for each city the number of poets who born there and who was educated there (the result set must be a list of triples city IRI, label and #poets).
goals.8: Return the italian poets who won the Nobel Prize in Literature (the result set must be poet IRI and label).

name: workflow1_3

1.narrative:
startup the evaluation
setup the file and create the empty json
look at the properties of The Divine Comedy
output: National Library of Israel J9U ID

1.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q40185 wdt:P50 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }

2.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 1 in the file
look at the Dante's occupations
2.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 wdt:P106 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }

3.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 2 in the file
look at the object properties of Dante
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?pr ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 ?pr ?obj . ?pr sc:name ?name. FILTER(!isLiteral(?obj)). }
output: on focus list of Wikimedia project

3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 wdt:P135 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }

3.narrative: find the class of Dolce Stil Novo
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?class ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 wdt:P135 ?obj . ?obj wdt:P31 ?class. ?class sc:name ?name. }

4.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 3 in the file
look at the place of birth of Dante
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?o ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 wdt:P19 ?o. ?o sc:name ?name. }

4.narrative: look at the date properties of Dante
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?pr ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 ?pr ?o. ?pr sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name, "date")). }

4.narrative: filter for poets born in Florence between 1300 and 1500
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?poet ?name WHERE { wd:Q1067 wdt:P570 ?dDeath. wd:Q1067 wdt:P569 ?dBirth. ?poet wdt:P19 wd:Q2044; wdt:P569 ?birth; wdt:P106 wd:Q49757. ?poet sc:name ?name. FILTER((year(?birth) > 1300) && (year(?birth) < 1500)). }

5.narrative: look at the properties of Dante
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?inst ?name WHERE { ?x wdt:P50 wd:Q1402. ?x wdt:P31 ?inst. ?inst sc:name ?name. }

6.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 5 in the file
find literary works of Dante and Boccaccio
6.query: SELECT ?poets ?name COUNT(?x) WHERE { VALUES ?poets {wd:Q1402 wd:Q1067}. ?x wdt:P50 ?poets. ?x wdt:P31 wd:Q7725634. ?poets sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?poets ?name

7.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
look at the properties of poets
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?pr ?name WHERE { ?poet wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; ?pr ?o. ?pr sc:name ?name. FILTER(!isLiteral(?o)). }
output: second family name in Spanish name
on focus list of Wikimedia project

said to be the same as
patronym or matronym for this person
contributor to the creative work or subject
category for the exterior of the item
first family name in Portuguese name
organization directed by the office or position

7.narrative: find for each Italian city the number of poets born and educated there
7.query: SELECT ?city ?name COUNT(?poet) AS ?poets WHERE { ?poet wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P19 ?city; wdt:P69 ?o. ?city wdt:P17 wd:Q38. ?o wdt:P131 ?city; wdt:P31 wd:Q3918. ?city sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?city ?name

8.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
look for Nobel Prize in Literature, starting
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?aw ?name WHERE { ?poet wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P19 ?city. ?city wdt:P17 wd:Q38. ?poet wdt:P166 ?aw. ?aw sc:name ?name. filter(REGEX(?name , "Nobel")). }

8.narrative: look at the properties of The Divine Comedy
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?poet ?name WHERE { ?poet wdt:P106 wd:Q49757; wdt:P19 ?city. ?city wdt:P17 wd:Q38. ?poet wdt:P166 wd:Q37922. ?poet sc:name ?name. }
